{"sectionId":675,"sectionIdLiteral":"675","humanId":"lesson-260","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"Let me remember God created me.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 260"},"annotation":"W-260","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-260\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"675#1\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"675#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Father, I did not make myself, although in my insanity I thought I did.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"675#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Yet, as Your Thought, I have not left my Source, remaining part of Who created me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"675#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Your Son, my Father, calls on You today.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"675#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Let me remember You created me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"675#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Let me remember my Identity.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"675#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>And let my sinlessness arise again before Christ‚Äôs vision, through which I would look upon my brothers and myself today.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"675#2\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"675#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Now is our Source remembered, and Therein we find our true Identity at last.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"675#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Holy indeed are we, because our Source can know no sin.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"675#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>And we who are His Sons are like each other, and alike to Him.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Father, I did not make myself, although in my insanity I thought I did. Yet, as Your Thought, I have not left my Source, remaining part of Who created me. Your Son, my Father, calls on You today. Let","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 260: Let me remember God created me | ACIM","seoDescription":